
[1]hebdomadary

   HEBDOM'ADARY, a. Weekly; consisting of seven days, or occurring every
   seven days.

   HEBDOM'ADARY, n. A member of a chapter or convent, whose week it is to
   officiate in the choir, rehearse the anthems and prayers, and perform
   other services, which on extraordinary occasions are performed by the
   superiors.
